│ THOUGHT: The tests fail because we changed IRBuilder’s insert point globally (via saveIP/restoreIP) even for    │
│ uniform broadcasts, which perturbs instruction ordering. To confine ordering changes strictly to the            │
│ non-uniform packing path, I will remove the global Builder.saveIP at the start and instead save and restore the │
│ insert point only within the non-uniform branch: save before adjusting the insertion point (just before         │
│ handling NewIP), and restore after finishing packing lanes. This keeps uniform broadcasts at their original     │
│ position and preserves CHECK-NEXT expectations, while still avoiding the end-iterator crash.                    │
